==English==

===Etymology===
From Dutch [[koekje]] (possibly through dialectal variation ''koekie''), diminutive of [[koek]]. Originally US English only, now common in Commonwealth English also.

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|/ko͝ok'i/}}
*{{IPA|/ˈkʊki/}}
*[[SAMPA]]: /<tt>"kUki</tt>/
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʊki|-ʊki]]

===Alternative spellings===
*[[cooky]] ''(UK)''
*[[cook-ie]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A small flat, baked cake which is either crisp or soft but firm (often with chocolate chips, candies or nuts mixed in.)
# (''computing'') A '''[[magic cookie]]'''.
# (''computing'') An '''[[HTTP cookie]]'''.

====Synonyms====
*(''cake'') [[biscuit]], [[bickie]] (''Commonwealth English'')

